template literal = ` ` instead of ' ' or " " - allows for multiple line
How to create a component:
    -Create 3 files:
        name.component.html
        name.component.css
        name.component.ts
    
    -3 requirements for Component Decorator
        1. selector = directive app-? e.g. app-nav, app-flashcard etc
        2. template or templateUrl - the html for this component
        3. style or stylesUrl - the css for this component

    -export the class
    -Add to the app.module.ts -declarations

How to map a route:
        1. component should be created
        2. Add url to Navbar HTML e.g. /js for JavaScript
        3. Add the path to YOUR AppRouter Module 
            (this you made and exported to the app.module.ts)

Pull Data from API
        1. Create Model (if needed)
        2. Create service or use an existing angular service
        3. Add service to the ngModel's provider 
        4. Inject into the components where needed
        5. Use ngOnInit for initialization data from service